# DTOs
Why are DTOs useful?
- They decouple pure logic from db schema details, allowing your database tables to evolve independently without 
breaking layers deep logic
- The allow pure functions to remain pure and not cause side effects especially if you are dealing with an 
active record pattern ORM (django)
- It allows you to gain significantly better type inference in dynamic languages that have magical frameworks (django)
- since they allow you to keep functions pure, you can also have mockless tests, much much easier to maintain and develop
 
